# Copy to .env for local builds (.env is gitignored). In CI these are GitHub Secrets,
# NOT committed. See README.md > Secrets.

# 境外 DNS. NextDNS "DNS-over-HTTPS" URL from your NextDNS setup page.
# Embeds your config id. In CI it is injected into the built config, which is published
# publicly on GitHub Pages -> so this URL is public by design (it only selects an ad-block
# config). Keep it out of the *source tree* regardless; set it only as the Actions secret.
NEXTDNS_DOH_URL=

# Delivery is GitHub Pages (see README > Delivery). No SSH/rsync secrets are needed.
